1 Section 1. NRS 209.511 is hereby amended to read as follows:
2 209.511 1. Before an offender is released from prison by
3 expiration of his or her term of sentence, by pardon or parole, the
4 Director may provide mediation services to the offender and the
5 family members and friends of the offender who provide emotional,
6 psychological and financial support to the offender.
7 2. As soon as practicable after an offender is authorized to
8 apply for enrollment in Medicaid pursuant to NRS 422.272428 or
9 422.27487, the Director shall complete the paperwork for the
10 application if the offender may be eligible for Medicaid:
11 (a) Not more than 90 days before the scheduled release of the
12 offender pursuant to NRS 422.272428; or
13 (b) Immediately upon the scheduled release of the offender
14 pursuant to NRS 422.27487.
15 3. Not later than 3 months before an offender is projected to be
16 released from prison by expiration of his or her term of sentence, by
17 pardon or parole, the Director may, if space is available, provide an
18 eligible offender with one or more evidence-based or promising
19 practice reentry programs to obtain employment, including, without
20 limitation, any programs which may provide bonding for an
21 offender entering the workplace and any organizations which may
22 provide employment or bonding assistance to such a person.
23 4. When an offender is released from prison by expiration of
24 his or her term of sentence, by pardon or by parole, the Director:
25 (a) May furnish the offender with a sum of money not to exceed
26 $100, the amount to be based upon the offender’s economic need as
27 determined by the Director;
28 (b) Shall give the offender notice of the provisions of chapter
29 179C of NRS and NRS 202.357 and 202.360;
30 (c) Shall require the offender to sign an acknowledgment of the
31 notice required in paragraph (b);
32 (d) Shall give the offender notice of the provisions of NRS
33 179.245 and the provisions of NRS 213.090, 213.155 or 213.157, as
34 applicable;
35 (e) Shall provide the offender with a photo identification card
36 issued by the Department and information and reasonable assistance
37 relating to acquiring a valid driver’s license or identification card to
38 enable the offender to obtain employment, if the offender:
39 (1) Requests a photo identification card;
40 (2) Requests such information and assistance and is eligible
41 to acquire a valid driver’s license or identification card from the
42 Department of Motor Vehicles; or
